Similarly for the second set:
`{x | p' x ∧ q' x} = {x | p' x} ∩ {x | q' x}`

Since `{x | p' x}` ∈ `𝓝 x` and `{x | q' x}` ∈ `𝓝 x`, their intersection is also in `𝓝 x`.

Then, the union of these two sets is also in `𝓝 x`.

So, here's the proof in Lean:

```tactics
have h1 : {x | p x ∧ q x} ∈ 𝓝 x := by
  have h2 : {x | p x} ∈ 𝓝 x := hT
  have h3 : {x | q x} ∈ 𝓝 x := hS
  have h4 : {x | p x} ∩ {x | q x} ∈ 𝓝 x := by
    exact Filter.mem_inter h2 h3
  have h5 : {x | p x ∧ q x} = {x | p x} ∩ {x | q x} := by
    ext y
    simp
  rw [h5] at *
  exact h4
